# React Component Patterns

- Functional components only — no class components
- Define and export props interfaces (e.g., `PokemonCardProps`, `SearchBarProps`)
- State management via React Context (`contexts/PokemonContext.tsx`) — no external state library
- Wrap async operations in try/catch and surface errors to users
- Modals must support Escape key dismiss and click-outside-to-close
- Use `useCallback` for functions passed as props or used in dependency arrays
- Use a `cancelled` flag pattern in `useEffect` to prevent state updates after unmount

```tsx
// Preferred error handling in async effects
try {
  const data = await fetchPokemonData(name);
  if (cancelled) return;
  setData(data);
} catch (err) {
  if (!cancelled) setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : "Unknown error");
}
```
